# Cursor Rules - Project Hub

**IMPORTANT: Before exploring the codebase, read the `.ai/` folder first!**

This project has comprehensive documentation in the `.ai/` directory:

- `.ai/README.md` - Project overview and quick reference
- `.ai/PROJECT_OVERVIEW.md` - Full system architecture  
- `.ai/BACKEND.md` - NestJS API structure, modules, services
- `.ai/FRONTEND.md` - Next.js pages, components, state management
- `.ai/API_REFERENCE.md` - All endpoints documented
- `.ai/FILE_MAP.md` - Directory structure and file purposes
- `.ai/RECENT_CHANGES.md` - Latest features and modifications

## Rules

1. Always read `.ai/README.md` before making changes
2. Check `.ai/RECENT_CHANGES.md` for latest state
3. Use `.ai/FILE_MAP.md` to locate files quickly
4. Follow existing patterns documented in `.ai/BACKEND.md` and `.ai/FRONTEND.md`

## Tech Stack

- **Backend**: NestJS + Prisma + PostgreSQL
- **Frontend**: Next.js 14 (App Router) + shadcn/ui + TailwindCSS
- **Auth**: Clerk

## Key Conventions

- Use barrel exports in services
- API functions in `client/lib/api.ts`
- Types in `client/types/index.ts`
- Components in `client/components/`
- Dashboard pages follow `/dashboard/[role]/[feature]/page.tsx` pattern
